Ok I'll let you build a front end that:
- Lets anyone buy a ticket with crypto or credit card
- Send a confirmation e-mail (only when tx has been confirmed)
- Asks for metada and encrypts it
- Allows for transfer of tickets (and update of associated metadata)

And also:
- A way for us to track the tickets that have been sold
- The possibility of creating different ticket categories
- Possibility for us to "check" a valid ticket (making it invalid)
- Possibility for us to extract all the metada from all the ticket easiliy
- Possibility for us to revoke a specific ticket
- Possibliity for people to buy multiple tickets and send them to other people from their team
- Possibility for us to manually add tickets last minute for special guests (think Vitalik etc)

And also:
- A very good and easy tutorial for people who are crypto noobs and come to the event just to know more about it
- Ideally a way to be inter-chain because if we publish all the tickets on Polygon, some people will complain that it's "not a true L2" (this is not mandatory but a bonus :p)

- UI needs to be really slick and simple (all the typical "switch network", or "you don't have enough gas" etc etc need to be handled properly because we WILL be dealing with crypto newbies :))
- This CAN'T mess up. We cannot take the risk of having a conference canceled because something went wrong with ticketing :p

Hi guys! Anybody knows how to send UST from Coinbase to a terra wallet?

UST from Coinbase will not go to to Terra it will go to ETH as an ERC 20 token.

Here is the process to get it on the terra blockchain-

You first need to send your UST to a wallet whose private key/seed phrase you own like metamask. So you need to withdraw your UST from Coinbase and then send it to this metamask address.

Use bridge.terra.money to move the UST in metamask to terra blockchain.

Just sell the UST in Coinbase for something like LTC/XLM (these coins require very little transaction fees).

Send LTC/XLM to Kucoin (you can make a Kucoin account without KYC if it doesn't allow you to just use VPN while making the account).

Now sell the LTC/XLM for UST.

Withdraw UST into Terrastation.

Hey folks - Iâ€™m Savva a commercial/IP/crypto/patent attorney and founder of DeSci project Crowd Funded Cures (crowdfundedcures.org), partnered with and advising VitaDAO, Molecule, PsyDAO and others. Our mission at CFC is to create marketplace for open source clinical trial data without patents by using IP-NFTs Pay-For-Success (PFS) smart contracts and crowdfunded Medical Impact Certificates to incentivise repurposing of generic drugs, nutraceuticals, plant medicines & psychedelics, diets and lifestyle interventions. We plan to launch as an Impact DAO to de-risk early stage research and Public Good Pharma company using PFS contracts to get regulatory approval and bring these products to market. A $50-100m incentive can create a drug worth over $1b eg repurposing fluvoxamine to treat covid or generic ketamine or psilocybin to treat major depression. My presentation at DeSci.Berlin here in May is a good summary https://youtu.be/GbIGnhmJh2w . For a deeper dive check out https://crowdfundedcures.medium.com/pay-for-success-contracts-a-new-model-to-develop-new-therapies-from-old-drugs-f69b2189184d.
